ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, the performance of multi-stimuli-responsive CDs@POSS-based LMs for the remote control of microfluidics is described in Fig. 4
                        . To demonstrate this, LMs were prepared by coating 10 μL droplets with CDs@POSS particles and suspended on water statically. External stimuli including electricity, light and magnetism were then applied respectively to induce movement of the LMs (Fig. 4a and Supplementary Videos). For a more in-depth understanding of the multi-stimuli-responsive process of CDs@POSS-based LMs, the mechanism of each external stimuli was explored (Fig. 5
                        ).
